title: Untitled
content:
import cv2
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt

# Загрузка изображения
image_path = 'path/to/your/image.jpg'
original_image = cv2.imread(image_path)

# Преобразование изображения в оттенки серого
gray_image = cv2.cvtColor(original_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)

# Ядро оператора Лапласса
laplacian_kernel = np.array([[0, 1, 0],
                             [1, -4, 1],
                             [0, 1, 0]])

# Применение оператора Лапласса к цветному изображению
sharp_color_image = cv2.filter2D(original_image, -1, laplacian_kernel)

# Применение оператора Лапласса к изображению в оттенках серого
sharp_gray_image = cv2.filter2D(gray_image, -1, laplacian_kernel)

# Отображение результатов
plt.subplot(1, 3, 1), plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(original_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)), plt.title('Original')
plt.subplot(1, 3, 2), plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(sharp_color_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)), plt.title('Sharp Color')
plt.subplot(1, 3, 3), plt.imshow(sharp_gray_image, cmap='gray'), plt.title('Sharp Gray')

plt.show()

title: Testing thread etc.
content:
#Based on: Sz. P.
import time
import math
from math import sqrt
import random
import threading

class tests:
    def __init__(self):
        self.lessthan1 = []
        self.lessthan2 = []
        self.lessthan3 = []
        self.lessthan4 = []
        self.tomb = []
    def withdot(self):
        starttime=time.time()
        for i in range(1,10000000):
            a=math.sqrt(i)
        print('withdot: \n',time.time()-starttime,'\n')

    def withoutdot(self):
        starttime=time.time()
        for i in range(1,10000000):
            a=sqrt(i)
        print('without dot:',time.time()-starttime,'\n')
   
    def loops(self):
        print('loops' ,'\n')
        self.tomb=random.sample(range(0, 100000000), 10000000)
        starttime=time.time()
        self.lessthan1=[i for i in self.tomb if i<50000000]
        
        print('Listiter:',time.time()-starttime ,'\n')
    def range(self):
        starttime=time.time()
        for i in range(0,len(self.tomb)):
            if self.tomb[i]<50000000:
                self.lessthan2.append(self.tomb[i])
        print('Range:   ',time.time()-starttime,"\n")
    def foreach(self):
        starttime=time.time()
        for i in self.tomb:
            if i<50000000:
                self.lessthan3.append(i)
        print('foreach: ',time.time()-starttime,"\n")
    def whileofwhile(self):
        i=0 
        starttime=time.time()
        while i<len(self.tomb):
            if self.tomb[i]<50000000:
                self.lessthan4.append(self.tomb[i])
            i+=1
        print('while:   ',time.time()-starttime,"\n")

test = tests()
test.withdot()
test.withoutdot()
test.loops()

test.range()
test.foreach()
test.whileofwhile()

print ("Experimental")


t1 = threading.Thread(target=test.withdot)
t2 = threading.Thread(target=test.withoutdot)
t3 = threading.Thread(target=test.loops)
t4 = threading.Thread(target=test.range)
t5 = threading.Thread(target=test.foreach)
t6 = threading.Thread(target=test.whileofwhile)
t1.start()
t2.start()
t1.join()
t2.join()
t3.start()
t4.start()
t5.start()
t6.start()

t3.join()
t4.join()
t5.join()
t6.join()
print("Test Finshed")

title: Chapter 5 Reign Of quantity Guenon
content:
CHaPter V
Qualitative Determinations of Time
Time seems to be even further away than space from pure quantity. It is possible to speak of both temporal and spatial quantities, and both belong to the continuous quantity (since it is not necessary to dwell on the strange conception of Descartes, according to which time would be constituted by a series of discontinuous instants, which makes it necessary to suppose a constantly renewed "creation", without which the world would disappear at every moment in the intervals of this discontinuity); but a great distinction must be made between the two cases, since, as we have already indicated, while space can be measured directly, time can only be measured by reducing it, as it were, to space.
What is really measured is never a duration, but the space covered during this duration in a certain movement whose law is known. By presenting this law as a relationship between time and space, we can, when we know the dimension of the covered space, deduce from it the dimension of the time used to cover it; and whatever artifacts we employ, after all there is no other means than this to determine temporal quantities.1
Another observation that also tends to the same conclusion is this: properly corporeal phenomena are the only ones that are located both in space and in time; phenomena of a mental nature, those studied by
"psychology" in the ordinary sense of the word, do not
have a spatial character, but instead also occur in time. If the nature of time allows it to be extended to the individual realm and hence
condition our own mental manifestations, then this nature must be even more qualitative than that of space. Since we are talking about mental phenomena, we will add that, insofar as they are on the side of what the essence represents in the individual, it is perfectly vain to look for quantitative elements in them; although some go so far that they try to reduce them to quantity. What the "psycho-physiologists" determine quantitatively are not actually the mental phenomena properly speaking, as they imagine them, but only some of their bodily concomitants; but there is nothing there that is in any way related to the very nature of the mind, nor therefore can serve to explain it in the least. The absurd idea of a quantitative psychology really represents the most accentuated degree of modern "scientistic" aberration!
According to all this, if we can speak of a "qualified" space, we are even more justified to speak of a "qualified" time. By this we mean that there must be fewer quantitative determinations in time and more qualitative determinations than in space. "Empty time" has no more effective existence than "empty space", and in this respect everything that we have said about space could be repeated. There is no more time than space outside our world, and in it realized time always contains events, just as realized space always contains bodies.
In certain aspects there is a kind of symmetry between space and time, being able to speak of them in parallel. But this symmetry, which is not found with respect to the other conditions of bodily ex-istence, is perhaps due more to its qualitative side than to the quantitative side, as tends to be demonstrated by the difference that we have indicated between the determination of spatial and quantitative temporal magnitudes, and also by the absence, as regards time, of a quantitative science of the same type as geometry is for space.
On the other hand, in the qualitative order, symmetry is expressed in a particularly remarkable way by the correspondence that exists between spatial symbolism and temporal symbolism, and of which we have had occasion to give examples elsewhere; as far as symbolism is concerned, in effect, it is evident that it is the consideration of quality that is essentially involved, and not that of quantity. It is evident that different periods of time are qualitatively differentiated by the events that occur in them, just as the portions of space are differentiated by the bodies they contain, and that we cannot in any way consider quantitatively similar durations, but filled by very different series of events; it is even a common observation that the quantitative equality, in the mental appreciation of the duration, disappears completely before the qualitative difference.
But it can be said that this difference is not inherent in duration itself, but only in what happens within it. We must therefore ask ourselves if there is not, on the contrary, in the qualitative determination of events, something that comes from time itself; and, indeed, do we not at least implicitly recognize that this is so when we speak, for example, as we constantly do even in ordinary language, of the particular conditions of one or other period?
This seems even more evident in the case of time than in that of space, although, as we have explained, the qualitative elements in the position of bodies are by no means negligible. And even if we wanted to get to the bottom of things, we could say that any body cannot be situated indifferently in any place, nor can any event occur indifferently at any time; but here the symmetry is not perfect, because the position of a body in space is susceptible to variation due to the fact of movement, while that of an event in time is strictly determined and is properly "unique", so that the essential nature of events seems to be much more strictly related to time than that of bodies to space, which further confirms that time must itself have a more broadly qualitative character.
The truth is that time is not something that develops in a uniform way and, therefore, its geometric representation by means of a straight line, as it is usually conceived by modern mathematicians, only gives a totally distorted idea of it, due to oversimplification. We shall see later that the tendency to oversimplify remains one of the characteristics of the modern mind and that, furthermore, it inevitably accompanies the tendency to reduce everything to quantity.
The true representation of time is provided by the traditional conception of cycles, a conception which, of course, is essentially that of a "qualified" time; furthermore, insofar as it is a geometric representa-tion, either made graphically or simply expressed by the terminology used, it is evident that it is an application of spatial symbolism, and this should give rise to the idea that we can find in it a indication of a certain correlation between qualitative determinations of time and space.
This is what happens; for space, these determinations reside essentially in directions; now the cyclical representation establishes precisely a correspondence between the phases of a temporal cycle and the directions of space. To convince ourselves of this, it is enough to consider an example taken from among the most simple and immediately accessible, that of the annual cycle, which plays, as is known, a very important role in traditional symbolism,2 in which the four seasons correspond to the four cardinal points?
It is not necessary to develop here a more or less complete exposition of the doctrine of the cycles, although it is naturally implied in the very substance of the present study. In order to stay within the limits that we must impose on ourselves, we will content ourselves for the moment with making some observations more directly related to our subject as a whole, reserving the right to resort later to other considerations related to the same doctrine.
The first of these observations is that not only each phase of a temporal cycle, whatever it may be, has its own quality that influences the determination of events, but even the speed with which they develop is something that also depends on these phases and therefore is qualitative rather than quantitative in nature.
Thus, when we speak of this speed of events in time, by analogy with the speed of a body moving in space, we must make a certain transposition of this notion of speed, which can no longer be reduced to a quantitative expression such as the one related to the speed properly said in mechanics.
What we mean is that, according to the different phases of the cycle, the series of events that are comparable to each other do not occur in quantitatively equal durations. This is especially clear when it comes to the great cycles, both cosmic and human, and one of the most notable examples is the decreasing proportion of the respective durations of the four Yugas, which together make up the Manvantara.4
Precisely for this reason, events now unfold with a speed unparalleled in earlier times, a speed that is constantly accelerating and which will continue to do so until the end of the cycle. There is here a kind of progressive "contraction" of duration, the limit of which corresponds to the "stopping point" to which we have already alluded; we will have to return to these considerations later and explain them in more detail.
The second observation refers to the descending direction of the cycle, insofar as it is considered as the chronological expression of a process of manifestation that implies a progressive departure from the beginning; but we have already talked about it often enough to do without dwelling on it again.
We mention this point again mainly because, in relation to what we have just said, it gives rise to a rather interesting spatial analogy: the increase in the speed of events as we approach the end of the cycle can be compared to the acceleration that exists in the falling motion of heavy bodies; the march of humanity today is truly similar to that of a mobile thrown down a slope, which moves all the faster the closer it is to the lowest point. Even if certain reactions in the opposite direction, insofar as they are possible, make things a little more complex, it is nevertheless a very exact picture of the cyclica movement taken in its generality.
Finally, our third observation. When the downward march of the manifestation takes place, and consequently that of the cycle that is an expression of it, from the positive or essential pole of existence towards its negative or substantial pole, it follows that all things must take on an aspect that is less and less qualitative and more and more quantitative; and that is why the last period of the cycle must particularly tend to assert itself as the "reign of quantity". Furthermore, when we say that this must occur in all things, we are not referring only to the way of seeing them from the human point of view, but also to a real change in the "environment" itself. Since each period in the history of humanity corresponds properly to a certain "cosmic moment" , there must necessarily be a constant correlation between the very state of the world, or what is called "nature" in the most common sense of the word, and more especially of the terrestrial environment as a whole, and that of humanity, whose existence is obviously conditioned by the latter.
We can add that the total ignorance of these cosmic modifications is not the least cause of the misunderstanding of profane science with respect to everything that is outside certain limits. Born of the very special conditions of the present time, this science is evidently completely incapable of conceiving other conditions different from these, or even of admitting that they may exist, and thus the very point of view that defines it establishes "barriers" in the time that are as impossible to cross as it would be for a nearsighted to see clearly beyond a certain distance; and indeed, the modern "scien-tistic" mentality is characterized in all respects by a true "intellectual myopia".
We will develop this topic further later, in order to better understand what these changes in the environment may be, to which for now we can only refer to in a very general way. Perhaps it is understood that many things that today are considered "fabulous" were not so at all for the ancients, and that they may not even be so for those who have preserved, with the deposit of certain traditional knowledge, the notions that allow them to reconstitute the figure of a "lost world" , as well as foreseeing what the future world will be like. The past and the future correspond analogously, so that regardless of what ordinary mortals think, such predictions are not actually "divinatory" in the least, but are based entirely on what we have called the qualitative determinations of time. 

Notes
1. Here Guénon obviously refers to mechanical analog clocks with hands.
This paragraph was written before there were digital quartz clocks, which measure time in a completely different way, based on the vibratory frequency of a quartz crystal, and which show the result of this measurement on a panel, where time it is not appreciated by the movement of a hand, but rather by the change of the digits that indicate the hour (TN).
2. We will limit ourselves here to recalling, on the one hand, the considerable scope of the symbolism of the Zodiac, especially from the strictly initiatory point of view, and on the other, the direct applications of a ritual nature to which the development of the annual cycle gives rise in most of the traditional forms.
3. We want to mention, with regard to the qualitative determinations of space and time and their correspondences, a testimony that is certainly not suspicious, since it is that of an "official" orientalist. Mr. Marcel Granet, who has dedicated a whole section of his work entitled La Pensée chinoise (Chinese thought) to these traditional notions. It goes without saying that the author only sees singularities in all this, which he tries to explain from a purely "psychological" and "sociological" point of view, but obviously we do not have to deal with this interpretation, which reflects modern prejudices in general and academics in particular, but it is the observation of the fact itself that is important to us here. In this sense, the book in question offers a striking image of the antithesis that a traditional civilization (and this would be equally true for any other than the Chinese) presents against the "quanti-tative" civilization of the modern West.
4. It is known that this proportion is that of the numbers 4, 3, 2, 1, whose total gives 10 for the whole cycle. It is also known that the duration of human life itself is considered to decrease from one age to another, which is to say that human life passes with increasing speed from the beginning of the cycle to its end.

#Requires AutoHotkey v2.0
#SingleInstance Force

; Prevent capslock from turning on when using as a modifier.
CapsLock::{
    KeyWait "CapsLock"
    if (A_ThisHotkey = "CapsLock")
        SetCapsLockState(GetKeyState("CapsLock", "T") ? "AlwaysOff" : "AlwaysOn")
}

class WindowManager {
    static max_grid_size := 4
    static current_col_count := 1
    static current_row_count := 1
    static Modifier := "CapsLock"

    static __New() {
        this.lineColor := "3CA4EA"
        this.overlay := Gui("+AlwaysOnTop -Caption +ToolWindow +E0x20")
        this.overlay.BackColor := "0C0C0C"
        WinSetTransparent(140, this.overlay)
        this.guides := Gui("+AlwaysOnTop -Caption +ToolWindow +E0x20 +Owner" this.overlay.hwnd)
        this.guides.BackColor := "FF00FF"
        WinSetTransColor(this.guides.BackColor " 220", this.guides)
        this.windowBorder := Gui("+AlwaysOnTop -Caption +ToolWindow +E0x20 +Owner" this.overlay.hwnd)
        this.windowBorder.BackColor := "237FD5"

        HotIf (*) => GetKeyState(this.modifier, "P")
        ; modifier + key
        Hotkey "*j", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "Move", 1))      ; Move left
        Hotkey "*i", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "Move", 2))      ; Move up
        Hotkey "*l", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "Move", 3))      ; Move right
        Hotkey "*k", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "Move", 4))      ; Move down
        Hotkey "*u", (*) => (Send("#+{Left}"), this.HideGuides())        ; move to previous monitor
        Hotkey "*o", (*) => (Send("#+{Right}"), this.HideGuides())       ; move to next monitor
        Hotkey "*m", (*) => this.IsWindowExcluded() || (WinMaximize("A"), this.HideGuides()) ; maximize
        ; modifier + shift + key
        Hotkey "*+j", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "Resize", 1))   ; decrease width
        Hotkey "*+i", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "Resize", 2))   ; decrease height
        Hotkey "*+l", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "Resize", 3))   ; increase width
        Hotkey "*+k", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "Resize", 4))   ; increase height
        ; modifier + alt + key
        Hotkey "*!i", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "ChangeRowCount", -1))   ; increase row count
        Hotkey "*!k", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "ChangeRowCount", 1))  ; decrease row count
        Hotkey "*!j", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "ChangeColCount", -1))  ; decrease col count
        Hotkey "*!l", HotkeyCallback(ObjBindMethod(this, "ChangeColCount", 1))   ; increase col count

        HotIf (*) => DllCall("IsWindowVisible", "ptr", this.guides.hwnd)
        Hotkey "*" this.modifier " Up", (*) => this.HideGuides()

        HotIf ; End hotif

        HotkeyCallback(callback) {
            ; If not excluded window, call the callback, and show guides if guides are not visible.
            return (*) => (this.IsWindowExcluded() || callback(this.GetCoords()), DllCall("IsWindowVisible", "ptr", this.guides.hwnd) || this.ShowGuides())
        }
    }

    static IsWindowExcluded(win:="A") => InStr("(Shell_TrayWnd|Shell_SecondaryTrayWnd|WorkerW|AutoHotkeyGUI|XamlExplorerHostIslandWindow)", WinGetClass(win))

    static ChangeRowCount(inc, coords) {
        this.current_row_count += inc
        if this.current_row_count < 1
            this.current_row_count := this.max_grid_size
        else if this.current_row_count > this.max_grid_size
            this.current_row_count := 1
        coords := this.GetCoords(coords)
        this.ShowGuides()
        return coords
    }

    static ChangeColCount(inc, coords) {
        this.current_col_count += inc
        if this.current_col_count > this.max_grid_size
            this.current_col_count := 1
        else if this.current_col_count < 1
            this.current_col_count := this.max_grid_size
        coords := this.GetCoords(coords)
        this.ShowGuides()
        return coords
    }

    static GetCoords(coords?) {
        SetWinDelay(-1)
        win := WinExist("A")
        if !IsSet(coords)
            WinGetPosEx(&winX, &winY, &winW, &winH, win)
        else
            winX := coords.X, winY := coords.Y, winW := coords.W, winH := coords.H

        if WinGetMinMax(win) = 1
            WinRestore(win)

        this.Mon := MonInfoFromWindow(win)
        this.blockWidth := (this.Mon.WAWidth / this.current_col_count)
        this.blockHeight := (this.Mon.WAHeight / this.current_row_count)

        ; Find closest X.
        X := Floor((WinX+1) / this.blockWidth) * this.blockWidth
        if winX > (X + this.blockWidth/2)
            X += this.blockWidth
        X := Min(Max(this.Mon.WALeft, X), this.Mon.WARight-this.blockWidth)

        ; Find closest Y.
        Y := Floor((WinY+1) / this.blockHeight) * this.blockHeight
        if winY > (Y + this.blockHeight/2)
            Y += this.blockHeight
        Y := Min(Max(this.Mon.WATop, Y), this.Mon.WABottom-this.blockHeight)

        ; Find closest W.
        Width := (Ceil(WinW / this.blockWidth) * this.blockWidth)
        if Width > (winW + this.blockWidth/2)
            Width -= this.blockWidth
        Width := Max(Min(Width+1, this.Mon.WARight - X), this.blockWidth)

        ; Find closest H.
        Height := (Ceil(WinH / this.blockHeight) * this.blockHeight)
        if Height > (winH + this.blockHeight/2)
            Height -= this.blockHeight
        Height := Max(Min(Height+1, this.Mon.WABottom - Y), this.blockHeight)

        return {
            X: X,
            Y: Y,
            W: Width,
            H: Height,
            R: X+Width,
            B: Y+Height
        }
    }

    static Move(dir, coords) {
        WinGetPosEx(&winX, &winY, &winW, &winH, "A")
        WinR := winX+winW, WinB := WinY+WinH
        tolerance := 4
        Aligned := Abs(winX - coords.X) < tolerance && Abs(winY - coords.Y) < tolerance
        switch dir {
        case 1: ; Left
            if this.current_col_count = 1 || (Aligned && coords.X = this.Mon.WALeft)
                coords.W -= this.blockWidth, coords := this.ChangeColCount(1, coords)
            if Aligned
                coords.X -= this.blockWidth
        case 2: ; Up
            if this.current_row_count = 1 || (Aligned && coords.Y = this.Mon.WATop)
                coords.H -= this.blockHeight, coords := this.ChangeRowCount(1, coords)
            if Aligned
                coords.Y -= this.blockHeight
        case 3: ; Right
            if this.current_col_count = 1 || (Aligned && Abs(this.Mon.WARight - coords.R) < tolerance)
                coords := this.ChangeColCount(1, coords)
            if Aligned
                coords.X += this.blockWidth
        case 4: ; Down
            if this.current_row_count = 1 || (Aligned && Abs(this.Mon.WABottom - coords.B) < tolerance)
                coords := this.ChangeRowCount(1, coords)
            if Aligned
                coords.Y += this.blockHeight
        }
        coords := this.GetCoords(coords)
        SetTimer () => this.ShowWindowBorders(coords), -1
        WinMoveEx(coords.X, coords.Y, coords.W, coords.H, "A")
    }

    static Resize(dir, coords) {
        switch dir {
        case 1: ; Left
            coords.W -= this.blockWidth
        case 2: ; Up
            coords.H -= this.blockHeight
        case 3: ; Right
            coords.W += this.blockWidth
        case 4: ; Down
            coords.H += this.blockHeight
        }
        coords := this.GetCoords(coords)
        SetTimer () => this.ShowWindowBorders(coords), -1
        WinMoveEx(coords.X, coords.Y, coords.W, coords.H, "A")
    }

    static ShowGuides() {
        borderSize := 2
        colLineCount := this.current_col_count + 1
        rowLineCount := this.current_row_count + 1
        RowsCompleted := colsCompleted := 0
        ; Draw grid
        loop {
            if A_Index <= rowLineCount {
                try rowLine := this.guides["row" A_Index]
                catch
                    rowLine := this.guides.Add("Text", "vrow" A_Index " Background" this.lineColor)
                y := this.blockHeight * (A_Index - 1)
                y := A_Index = rowLineCount ? y - BorderSize : A_Index > 1 ? y - BorderSize/2 : y
                rowLine.Move(0, y, this.Mon.WAWidth, borderSize), rowLine.Visible := 1
            } else {
                try this.guides["row" A_Index].Visible := 0
                catch
                    rowsCompleted := 1
            }
        } Until RowsCompleted = 1

        loop {
            if A_Index <= colLineCount {
                try colLine := this.guides["col" A_Index]
                catch
                    colLine := this.guides.Add("Text", "vcol" A_Index " Background" this.lineColor)
                x := this.blockWidth * (A_Index - 1)
                x := A_Index = colLineCount ? x - borderSize : A_Index > 1 ? x - borderSize/2 : x
                colLine.Move(x, 0, borderSize, this.Mon.WAHeight), colLine.Visible := 1
            } else {
                try this.guides["col" A_Index].Visible := 0
                catch
                    colsCompleted := 1
            }
        } Until colsCompleted = 1
        this.guides.Show("NA x" this.Mon.WALeft " y" this.Mon.WATop " w" this.Mon.WAWidth " h" this.Mon.WAHeight)
        this.overlay.Show("NA x" this.Mon.WALeft " y" this.Mon.WATop " w" this.Mon.WAWidth " h" this.Mon.WAHeight)
    }

    static ShowWindowBorders(coords) {
        b := 4 ; bordersize
        , X := coords.X - this.Mon.Left, Y := coords.Y - this.Mon.WATop, Right := X + coords.W, Bottom := Y + coords.H
        ; Cut out window from overlay
        WinSetRegion("0-0 " this.Mon.WAWidth "-0 " this.Mon.WAWidth "-" this.Mon.WAHeight " 0-" this.Mon.WAHeight " 0-0 "
        			. X "-" Y " " Right "-" Y " " Right "-" Bottom " " X "-" Bottom " " X "-" Y, this.overlay)
        ; Draw border using WinSetRegion.
        WinSetRegion(X "-" Y " " Right "-" Y " " Right "-" Bottom " " X "-" Bottom " " X "-" Y " "
                   . X+b "-" Y+b " " Right-b "-" Y+b " " Right-b "-" Bottom-b " " X+b "-" Bottom-b " " X+b "-" Y+b, this.windowBorder)
        this.windowBorder.Show("NA x" this.Mon.WALeft " y" this.Mon.WATop " w" this.Mon.WAWidth " h" this.Mon.WAHeight)
    }

    static HideGuides(*) {
        this.windowBorder.Hide(), this.guides.Hide(), this.overlay.Hide()
        for ctrl in this.guides
            ctrl.Visible := 0
    }
}

; move window and fix offset from invisible border
WinMoveEx(x?, y?, w?, h?, hwnd?) {
    if !(hwnd is integer)
        hwnd := WinExist(hwnd)
    if !IsSet(hwnd)
        hwnd := WinExist()

    ; compare pos and get offset
    WinGetPosEx(&fX, &fY, &fW, &fH, hwnd)
    WinGetPos(&wX, &wY, &wW, &wH, hwnd)
    diffX := fX - wX
    diffY := fY - wY
    diffW := fW - wW
    diffH := fH - wH
    ; new x, y, w, h with offset corrected.
    IsSet(x) && nX := x - diffX
    IsSet(y) && nY := y - diffY
    IsSet(w) && nW := w - diffW
    IsSet(h) && nH := h - diffH
    WinMove(nX?, nY?, nW?, nH?, hwnd?)
}

; get window position without the invisible border
WinGetPosEx(&x?, &y?, &w?, &h?, hwnd?) {
    static DWMWA_EXTENDED_FRAME_BOUNDS := 9

    if !(hwnd is integer)
        hwnd := WinExist(hwnd)
    if !IsSet(hwnd)
        hwnd := WinExist() ; last found window

    DllCall('dwmapi\DwmGetWindowAttribute',
            'Ptr' , hwnd,
            'UInt', DWMWA_EXTENDED_FRAME_BOUNDS,
            'Ptr' , RECT := Buffer(16, 0),
            'Int' , RECT.size,
            'UInt')
    x := NumGet(RECT,  0, 'Int')
    y := NumGet(RECT,  4, 'Int')
    w := NumGet(RECT,  8, 'Int') - x
    h := NumGet(RECT, 12, 'Int') - y
}

MonInfoFromWindow(hwnd) {
    hMon := DllCall("MonitorFromWindow", "ptr", WinExist(hwnd), "uint", 2, "ptr")
    NumPut("uint", 40, mi := Buffer(40))
    DllCall("user32\GetMonitorInfo", "ptr", hMon, "ptr", mi)
    return {Left     : L  := NumGet(mi,  4, "int")
          , Top      : T  := NumGet(mi,  8, "int")
          , Right    : R  := NumGet(mi, 12, "int")
          , Bottom   : B  := NumGet(mi, 16, "int")
          , WALeft   : WL := NumGet(mi, 20, "int")
          , WATop    : WT := NumGet(mi, 24, "int")
          , WARight  : WR := NumGet(mi, 28, "int")
          , WABottom : WB := NumGet(mi, 32, "int")
          , Width    : Width  := R - L
          , Height   : Height := B - T
          , WAWidth  : WR - WL
          , WAHeight : WB - WT
          , Primary  : NumGet(mi, 36, "uint")
    }
}

--If you use this program in a video/post, I would greatly appreciate it if you would credit my Youtube channel https://www.youtube.com/c/Cod0fDuty.
--Please let me know if you have any questions or suggestions, feel free to contact me at cod0fdutyt@gmail.com.


local apiName = "touchpoint"
local pasteLink = "pFHeia96"
local infoName = "info"

term.clear()
term.setCursorPos(1,1)

if not fs.exists(apiName) then
   shell.run("pastebin get " .. pasteLink .. " " .. apiName)   --downloads the API
end

os.loadAPI(apiName)
peripheral.find("modem", rednet.open)
local monitor = peripheral.find("monitor")
monitor.setTextScale(0.5)
monitor.clear()

local monitorWidth, monitorHeight = monitor.getSize()
if monitorWidth >= 36 and monitorHeight >= 24 then   --changes text scale depending on the monitor size
   monitor.setTextScale(1)
   monitorWidth, monitorHeight = monitor.getSize()
end

local monitorSide
for _,name in ipairs(peripheral.getNames()) do   --gets the side the monitor is on
   if peripheral.getType(name) == "monitor" then
      monitorSide = name
   end
end

term.clear()
term.setCursorPos(1,1)
print("A ComputerCraft Program by Cod0fDuty")
print("Touchpoint API by Lyqyd")
print("Elevator Screen Module")

local floor = ""
local id = ""
local currentPage

while not fs.exists(infoName) or not floor or not id do   --check if file exists
   term.setCursorPos(1,6)
   term.clearLine()
   term.setCursorPos(1,5)
   term.clearLine()
   local h = fs.open("info", "w")
   term.write("Total number of floors: ")
   floor = tonumber(read())
   term.write("ID of receiving computer: ")
   id = tonumber(read())
   currentPage = 1
   local infoTable = {floor, id, currentPage}
   h.write(textutils.serialize(infoTable))
   h.close()
end

local h = fs.open(infoName, "r")   --reads from a file
local infoTable = textutils.unserialize(h.readAll())
if not infoTable then
   fs.delete(infoName)
   os.reboot()
end
floor = tonumber(infoTable[1])
id = tonumber(infoTable[2])
currentPage = tonumber(infoTable[3])
term.setCursorPos(1,5)
print("Total number of floors: " .. floor)
print("ID of receiving computer: " .. id)
h.close()

local buttonsPerColumn = math.floor((monitorHeight)/2)
local numberOfColumns = math.min(math.ceil(floor/buttonsPerColumn), 3)
local maxButtonsInOnePage = buttonsPerColumn * 3
local numberOfPages = math.ceil(floor/maxButtonsInOnePage)
local buttonWidth = monitorWidth - 2

if floor * 2 >= monitorHeight then
   buttonWidth = math.floor((monitorWidth-numberOfColumns - 3)/numberOfColumns)   --calculates the width of buttons
end

if currentPage > numberOfPages then   --if monitor size is changed, current page will be set to the maximum number of pages
   currentPage = numberOfPages
end

local page = {}
for i = 1, numberOfPages do
   page[i] = touchpoint.new(monitorSide)   --add pages
   if i ~= numberOfPages then
      page[i]:add(">>", nil, monitorWidth-3, monitorHeight, monitorWidth, monitorHeight, colors.black, colors.white)
   end
   if i ~= 1 then
      page[i]:add("<<", nil, 1, monitorHeight, 4, monitorHeight, colors.black, colors.white)
   end
   if numberOfPages > 1 then
      local pageLabel
      if monitorWidth == 15 then
         pageLabel = "P." .. i
      else                      --add page number
         pageLabel = "Page " .. i
      end
      page[i]:add(pageLabel, nil, 5, monitorHeight, monitorWidth-4, monitorHeight, colors.black, colors.black)
   end
end

local minX = 2
local minY = 1
local maxX = monitorWidth - 1
local maxY = minY

local pageIndex = 1
local topFloor = floor - 1

if topFloor < buttonsPerColumn then
   for i = topFloor, 0, -1 do
      page[pageIndex]:add(tostring(i), nil, minX, minY, maxX, maxY, colors.red, colors.lime)   --adds buttons in reverse
      minY = minY + 2
      maxY = minY
   end
else
   minX = 2
   maxX = minX + buttonWidth
   minY = monitorHeight - 1
   maxY = minY
   for i = 0, topFloor do
      page[pageIndex]:add(tostring(i), nil, minX, minY, maxX, maxY, colors.red, colors.lime)
      local remainingFloors = topFloor - i
      minY = maxY - 2
      maxY = minY
      if maxY <= 0 then   --move buttons to the next column
         minX = maxX + 2
         maxX = minX + buttonWidth
         minY = monitorHeight - 1
         maxY = minY
         if maxX > monitorWidth then   --change to next page
            pageIndex = pageIndex + 1
            minX = 2
            maxX = minX + buttonWidth
            minY = monitorHeight - 1
            maxY = minY
         end
         if remainingFloors < buttonsPerColumn then   --moves the buttons up if there are spaces
            minY = monitorHeight - 1 - ((buttonsPerColumn - remainingFloors) * 2)
            maxY = minY
         end
      end
   end
end

term.setCursorPos(1,8)
print("Press E to clear data...")

while true do
   page[currentPage]:draw()   --draws the buttons on the monitor
   local h = fs.open(infoName, "w")
   local infoTable = {floor, id, currentPage}
   h.write(textutils.serialize(infoTable))
   h.close()
   local event, p1 = page[currentPage]:handleEvents(os.pullEvent())
   if event == "button_click" then   --wait for button clicks
      local chosen = tonumber(p1)
      page[currentPage]:flash(p1)
      if chosen ~= nil then
         rednet.send(id, chosen, "call")
		 rs.setOutput("right", true)
      elseif p1 == ">>" then
         currentPage = currentPage + 1
      elseif p1 == "<<" then
         currentPage = currentPage - 1
      end
   elseif event == "key" and p1 == keys.e then
      fs.delete(infoName)   --deletes the file
      term.setCursorPos(1,9)
      print("Cleared!")
      sleep(1)
      os.reboot()
   end
end

local scSide = "left"
local stoSide = "right"

local sto = peripheral.wrap(stoSide)
local sc = peripheral.wrap(scSide)
local mw = 51
local mh = 16

local topBar = window.create(term.current(),1 ,1 ,mw,1)
local win = window.create(term.current(), 1,2,mw,mh)

local pageIndex = 0
local inPageIndex = 0
local pageCount = 0
local itemCount = 0
local listSize = 0

local winNormColor = {
    font = colors.black,
    bg = colors.lime
}

local winFocusColor = {
    font = colors.gray,
    bg = colors.pink
}

topBar.setBackgroundColor(colors.orange)
topBar.setTextColor(colors.white)
win.setBackgroundColor(winNormColor.bg)
win.setTextColor(winNormColor.font)

local nList = {}

local function LDebug(str,col)
    term.setCursorPos(1,col)
    term.setTextColor(colors.orange)
    term.setBackgroundColor(colors.white)
    term.clearLine()
    term.write(str)
end
local function paraseCMD() 

end

local function renewTopBar()
    local str = string.format("%3d/%3d      size:%d",pageIndex,pageCount,itemCount)
    topBar.clear()
    topBar.setCursorPos(1,1)
    topBar.write(str)
end

-- index, name
local winList = {}

local function renewWindow()
    win.clear()
    local s = 0
    for i,j in pairs(winList) do
        win.setCursorPos(1,i)
        if(i == inPageIndex) then
            win.setBackgroundColor(winFocusColor.bg)
            win.setTextColor(winFocusColor.font)
            win.clearLine()
        else
            win.setBackgroundColor(winNormColor.bg)
            win.setTextColor(winNormColor.font)
        end

        s = string.find(j[2],":")
        win.write(i..string.sub(j[2],s+1))
    end
    win.setBackgroundColor(winNormColor.bg)
    win.setTextColor(winNormColor.font)
end
local function re_count()
    itemCount = table.getn(nList)
    pageCount = (itemCount - itemCount % mh)/mh
    if(itemCount % mh ~= 0) then
        pageCount = pageCount +1
    end
end
local function re_scan()
    tList = sc.list()
    for i,j in pairs(tList) do
        table.insert(nList,{i, j.name})
    end
    for i,j in pairs(nList) do
        if(j[2] == nil ) then
            table.remove(nList,i)
        end
    end
    re_count()
    pageIndex = 1
    inPageIndex = 1
end

local function sub_scan()

end

local function pageChange()
    winList = {}
    local tMod = itemCount % mh
    if (pageIndex == pageCount and tMod ~= 0) then
        listSize = tMod
    else listSize = mh end
    local pos = (pageIndex - 1) * mh
    LDebug("listSize "..listSize.."itemCOunt "..itemCount, 19)
    for i=1,listSize,1 do
        repeat 
            pos = pos + 1
            if(pos > itemCount) then
                break
            end
        until(nList[pos]~=nil)
        if(pos > itemCount) then
            break
        end
        table.insert(winList,{nList[pos][1], nList[pos][2]})
    end
    LDebug("endPos "..pos,18)
    if(inPageIndex > listSize)then
        inPageIndex = listSize
    end
end

local function List_move()
    local pos = winList[inPageIndex][1]
    sc.pushItems(stoSide,pos)
    for i,j in pairs(nList) do
        if(j[1] == pos) then
            table.remove(nList,i)
        end
    end
    -- table.remove(nList,pageIndex * mh + inPageIndex)

    re_count()
   
    if(pageIndex >= pageCount) then
        pageIndex = pageCount
        if(inPageIndex <= itemCount % mh) then
            inPageIndex = itemCount % mh
        end
    end
    pageChange()
    renewTopBar()
    renewWindow()
end

local function init()
    re_scan()
    -- gen winList
    pageChange()

    renewTopBar()
    renewWindow()
end

local function mainloop()
term.clear()
init()
while true do
    term.setCursorPos(1,18)
    term.setTextColour(colors.white)
    local cmd = io.read()
    term.clearLine()
    term.write(winList[inPageIndex][1])
    term.write(winList[inPageIndex][2])
    List_move()
    
end
end
local keyMap = {
    ["end"]=(function () 
        if(inPageIndex < mh and inPageIndex <= listSize) then
            inPageIndex = inPageIndex + 1
            -- LDebug("nowPos "..(pageIndex-1) * mh + inPageIndex,18)
            renewWindow()
        end
    end),
    ["home"]=(function () 
        if(inPageIndex > 1) then
            inPageIndex = inPageIndex - 1
        -- LDebug("nowPos "..(pageIndex-1) * mh + inPageIndex,18)
        renewWindow()
        end
    end),
    ["pageUp"]=(function ()
        if(pageIndex > 1) then
            inPageIndex = 1
            pageIndex = pageIndex - 1
            pageChange()
            renewTopBar()
            renewWindow()
        end
    end),
    ["pageDown"]=(function () 
        if(pageIndex < pageCount) then
            inPageIndex = 1
            pageIndex = pageIndex + 1
            pageChange()
            renewTopBar()
            renewWindow()
        end
    end),
}

local function key_check()
while true do
    local event, key, isHeld = os.pullEvent("key")
    local kvalue = keys.getName(key)
    if(keyMap[kvalue]~= nil) then 
        keyMap[kvalue]() 
        term.setTextColour(colors.white)
        term.setCursorPos(1,18)
    end
end
end
parallel.waitForAny(mainloop,key_check)

title: Axyadix-02
content:
--Wolfbet
--Axyadix-02

basebet = 0.00001000
nextbet = basebet
payoutf = 17
payout  = payoutf
chance  = 99/payout
nextbet = basebet
ctlose  = 0

function increase(x,y)
    return x+(x*(y/100))
end

function decrease(x,y)
    return x-(x*(y/100))
end

resetstats()
function dobet()
    
    nextbet = increase(nextbet,7)
    if win then
        ctlose  = 0
        nextbet = basebet
        payout  = payoutf
    else
        ctlose += 1
        nextbet = increase(nextbet,10)
        if (ctlose < 11) then
            payout = decrease(payout,5.5)
        end
        if (ctlose ==11) then
            payout = 6.88
        end
    end
    chance = 99/payout
end

title: Axyadix-01
content:
--Wolfbet
--Axyadix

basebet = 0.00001248
nextbet = basebet
payoutf = 8.88
payout  = payoutf
chance  = 99/payout
nextbet = basebet
ctlose  = 0

resetstats()

function dobet()
    nextbet = nextbet+(nextbet*(22/100))
    if bets%2  == 0 then
        nextbet = nextbet+(nextbet*(22/100))
    end
    if bets%3  == 0 then
        nextbet = nextbet+(nextbet*(6.6/100))
    end
    if win then
        ctlose  = 0
        nextbet = basebet
        payout  = payoutf
    else
        ctlose += 1
        nextbet = nextbet+(nextbet*(51/100))
        if (ctlose < 5) then
            payout = payout-1.35
        end
        if (ctlose == 5) then
            payout = payout-0.26
        end
    end
    chance = 99/payout
end
